  • org.aksw.deer.util.OperatorFactory 
    Modifier and Type Constant Field Value
    public static final String CLONE_OPERATOR "clone"
    public static final String CLONE_OPERATOR_DESCRIPTION "The idea behind the clone operator is to enable parallel execution of different enrichment in the same dataset. The clone operator takes one dataset as input and produces n \u2265 2 output datasets, which are all identical to the input dataset. Each of the output datasets of the clone operator has its own execution (as to be input to any other enrichment or operator). Thus, DEER is able to execute all workflows of output datasets in parallel."
    public static final String MERGE_OPERATOR "merge"
    public static final String MERGE_OPERATOR_DESCRIPTION "The idea behind the merge operator is to enable combining datasets. The merge operator takes a set of n \u2265 2 input datasets and merges them into one output dataset containing all the input datasets\u2019 triples. As in case of clone operator, the merged output dataset has its own execution (as to be input to any other enrichment or operator)."
